<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870702-0170 </DOCNO><HL> Trinova Unit CompletesPurchase of British Firm</HL><DD> 07/02/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> TNVTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> MAUMEE, Ohio  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Trinova Corp. said its Sterling Engineered Products subsidiary completed the previously reported acquisition of the Fraser andamp; Glass division of Tenby Industries for #17 million ($27.5 million). Tenby is a unit of British-based Emess Lighting PLC.    Sterling manufacturers molded plastic products, decorative laminates and specialty resins. Fraser andamp; Glass makes injection-molded plastic parts, primarily for the European automotive industry.    In addition to its plastics business, Trinova makes power-control and motion-control products for fluid-system applications. </TEXT></DOC>